Finch SC(1).

Author information:
(1)Cooper Hospital, Camden, New Jersey, USA.

Probably more has been learned about radiation-induced leukemia from intensive 
study of Japanese atomic bomb survivors than about radiation damage to any other 
organ system. This has been the result of an intensive binational effort at the 
Atomic Bomb Casualty Commission and the Radiation Effects Research Foundation in 
Hiroshima and Nagasaki to monitor the occurrence of leukemia in a large group of 
