Update on primary osteoporosis.

Hurley DL(1), Khosla S.

Author information:
(1)Division of Endocrinology, Metabolism, Nutrition and Internal Medicine, Mayo 
Clinic Rochester, Minnesota 55905, USA.

Osteoporosis is the most common bone disorder encountered in clinical practice. 
It is also one of the most important diseases facing our aging population. In 
the United States alone, an estimated 1.5 million fractures that occur annually 
are attributed to osteoporosis, and they account for an estimated $13 billion 
annually. With the projected increase in life expectancy for the global 
population, osteoporosis and osteoporosis-related fractures have the potential 
to become an even larger health-care problem in the future. This article focuses 
on the evaluation and treatment of primary osteoporosis in women.

